Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @Poblano Pepper{2}(halved lengthwise) lengthwise; remove ribs and seeds. Drizzle
each half with @Cooking Oil{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place poblanos on a #baking sheet{} and roast on middle rack until softened,
~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and quarter @Lime{1}(zested and quartered) (for 4 servings, zest one
lime and quarter both). Halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1}(diced). Dice
@Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Mince @Chili Pepper{1}(minced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} and lime zest to taste. Add
water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with
salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @Riced Cauliflower{12%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, half the
tomato, 1/4 cup water, 3/4 tsp salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, use 1/3 cup water
and 1 1/2 tsp salt.) Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

Once poblanos are done roasting, stuff each half with as much filling as will fit.
Nestle into pan with remaining filling.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer filling and stuffed poblanos to a small
> baking dish.

Sprinkle poblano halves with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Bake on middle rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @Guacamole{4%tablespoon} in a #medium bowl{}; mix with remaining
tomato and lime juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide remaining filling and stuffed poblanos between plates. Top with guacamole,
crema, and chili if desired. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

== Zesty Crema ==

Combine @Sour Cream{} and @Lime{}(zested) to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until
mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.